WEBVTT

00:01.127 --> 00:03.505
LEDA will be dismantled for its assets.

00:03.630 --> 00:07.258
<i>Sarah and her self-aware sisters</i>

00:07.425 --> 00:08.760
<i>won't get such humane treatment.</i>

00:08.927 --> 00:11.513
Alison is Sarah's twin sister.

00:11.846 --> 00:13.973
Your bail hearing's
not going to be until Monday.

00:14.057 --> 00:15.100
- Monday?
- Mmm-hmm.

00:15.266 --> 00:17.227
- DOCTOR: Shingles.
- Yes.

00:17.352 --> 00:19.413
You'll be the first to take
the new generation of bot this week.

00:19.437 --> 00:21.117
Those shingles will be
a thing of the past.

00:21.147 --> 00:24.442
- A swan?
- Stop saying it like that.

00:24.859 --> 00:26.736
<i>It was a vision of a swan.</i>

00:27.987 --> 00:29.781
What is happening to me?

00:29.989 --> 00:31.616
- This is from my ma.
- No, no, no, no!

00:32.200 --> 00:34.077
What if we created a blastocyst?

00:34.327 --> 00:36.162
We'd need fertilizable LEDA eggs.

00:36.371 --> 00:37.956
And castor sperm from Ira.

00:38.039 --> 00:39.639
Where are you going to
get the eggs from?

00:39.666 --> 00:42.293
The only problem is
we don't have the resources to do it...

00:42.460 --> 00:43.461
Alone.

00:43.753 --> 00:45.839
I want to work with Sarah Manning

00:45.922 --> 00:48.842
and the others to restore you
as the head of Neolution.

00:48.967 --> 00:51.219
Are you sure you can work with Sarah?

00:51.511 --> 00:53.096
I look forward to it.

00:53.304 --> 00:54.723
I just want you to find a cure.

00:55.056 --> 00:56.057
We will.

01:30.133 --> 01:32.510
- (RACHEL BREATHING HEAVILY)
- Rachel?

01:36.556 --> 01:38.224
I saw it again.

01:39.184 --> 01:40.977
(SIGHS) The same man.

01:41.895 --> 01:45.190
- I think I was on the island.
- Are you all right?

01:46.399 --> 01:47.859
Yes, I'm fine.

01:48.818 --> 01:51.654
- It's fine.
- You need to see this.

01:54.991 --> 01:56.034
Turn it up.

01:57.160 --> 02:00.455
EVIE: <i>When the refinery shut down,
my father lost his job,</i>

02:00.538 --> 02:02.540
<i>just like a lot of folks in Tisdale.</i>

02:02.665 --> 02:04.584
<i>You had a serious illness, too,
didn't you?</i>

02:04.709 --> 02:06.336
<i>Severe combined immunodeficiency?</i>

02:06.419 --> 02:07.754
EVIE: <i>That's right.</i>

02:07.879 --> 02:10.715
We couldn't move.
Instead, it was a steady stream of

02:10.840 --> 02:13.718
of goodbyes, friends, teachers...

02:13.843 --> 02:15.029
That must have been difficult.

02:15.053 --> 02:16.554
I got through it.

02:16.679 --> 02:20.183
<i>But, as you know,
Tisdale is still suffering.</i>

02:20.266 --> 02:24.312
<i>So when Brightborn decided to
build a new research facility,</i>

02:24.395 --> 02:25.438
<i>I knew just the place.</i>

02:25.563 --> 02:27.166
INTERVIEWER: <i>Two hundred
and sixty new jobs,</i>

02:27.190 --> 02:28.900
<i>- a new walk-in clinic...</i>
- (CHUCKLES)

02:29.025 --> 02:32.862
She's painting herself
as some kind of hometown hero.

02:32.946 --> 02:34.155
Yeah, she's ingenious.

02:34.239 --> 02:36.241
<i>I believe Tisdale can rebuild.</i>

02:36.366 --> 02:40.119
<i>And here at Brightborn,
we just want to be a part of that.</i>

02:40.245 --> 02:42.515
Right, so it's press conference
day today. Give me something.

02:42.539 --> 02:43.873
What are you going to say?

02:45.542 --> 02:47.210
It's just another big
step for Brightborn.

02:47.293 --> 02:48.729
- You'll just have to wait and see.
- (BOTH CHUCKLE)

02:48.753 --> 02:50.564
You can probably give me one thing?
Just one little...

02:50.588 --> 02:52.188
- Just give me one thing.
- (EVIE LAUGHS)

02:52.257 --> 02:54.592
Her government approvals
have come through. (SIGHS)

02:54.717 --> 02:56.761
- Then we should act now.
- (KNOCKING ON DOOR)

02:57.971 --> 02:59.472
That's them.

02:59.597 --> 03:01.391
Are you sure you're all right?

03:13.278 --> 03:17.407
Scarcely believed it.
A CASTOR who favors slacks.

03:17.490 --> 03:20.285
- You must be Felix.
- Hello, Rachel.

03:20.410 --> 03:22.412
- Thank you for coming, Felix.
- (DOOR CLOSES)

03:23.121 --> 03:25.290
This is a bad idea.

03:27.959 --> 03:29.961
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)

04:30.521 --> 04:31.689
(DEER FALLS)

04:38.363 --> 04:40.239
GIRL: Mom, Mom, slow down!

04:40.365 --> 04:41.491
I think I saw a deer.

04:41.574 --> 04:43.326
- Where?
- Do you see something?

04:43.409 --> 04:45.409
WOMAN: Oh, I think I see it.
GIRL: Mom, look, look!

04:47.580 --> 04:48.790
GIRL: Oh, my gosh.

04:48.873 --> 04:50.875
- Mom! Oh, my gosh!
- BOY: Mom, it's a Sasquatch!

04:51.000 --> 04:53.187
MAN: No, it's just a girl.
GIRL: Oh, my gosh, she killed a deer!

04:53.211 --> 04:55.129
BOY: Oh, Mommy! Mom! Oh!

04:55.213 --> 04:56.506
GIRL: Mom, she killed a deer!

04:56.589 --> 04:58.233
WOMAN: Away from the window.
Away from the window.

04:58.257 --> 04:59.968
(INDISTINCT CLAMORING)

05:00.051 --> 05:01.928
WOMAN: Drive the damn car.
MAN: Oh, jeez.

05:05.556 --> 05:06.724
(HELENA HUMMING)

05:16.275 --> 05:17.360
(GRUNTS)

05:20.071 --> 05:21.698
I'm sure we can all agree

05:21.781 --> 05:25.493
that this little diplomatic exchange
is rock bottom.

05:25.576 --> 05:27.996
Susan gets the brilliant
and delightful Cosima

05:28.079 --> 05:30.456
forging ahead to save your lives,

05:30.581 --> 05:32.500
while we get you, Rachel,

05:32.583 --> 05:35.086
and your half-baked plan
to take down Evie Cho.

05:35.211 --> 05:37.296
I can assure you,
it is not half-baked...

05:37.422 --> 05:39.382
Ira, you fertilized
my sister's eggs for science.

05:39.465 --> 05:42.301
- You don't get to speak, too.
- SARAH: So what does it mean, then?

05:42.427 --> 05:46.055
Evie's got approval for
clinical trials of the new bot?

05:46.139 --> 05:49.058
It means implanted gene therapy works.

05:49.142 --> 05:52.562
They'll prove it suppresses
certain genetic disorders,

05:52.645 --> 05:54.397
only it's a Trojan horse.

05:54.480 --> 05:56.858
'Cause they can alter their DNA
however they want.

05:56.941 --> 05:58.067
Yes,

05:58.151 --> 06:00.236
including germline editing.

06:00.319 --> 06:04.198
Changing their clients' children's DNA
without consent.

06:04.282 --> 06:07.910
She wants to get the technology
to the public within three years.

06:07.994 --> 06:09.370
Jesus.

06:09.454 --> 06:11.914
Evie Cho might be
a more cunning villain than you, Rachel.

06:12.790 --> 06:15.084
Her villainy is exactly how we get her.

06:16.586 --> 06:17.879
Go on.

06:17.962 --> 06:21.340
IRA: Evie developed her tech
with illegal human trials.

06:21.466 --> 06:23.301
We've learned that two carriers

06:23.426 --> 06:25.970
recently fled
the Brightborn maternity lab.

06:26.471 --> 06:29.140
Tabitha Stewart and Kendra Dupree.

06:29.265 --> 06:30.892
You want to find them before Evie does?

06:30.975 --> 06:32.477
No, we want you to.

06:33.686 --> 06:35.313
With what these girls know,

06:35.438 --> 06:37.440
- I can destroy Evie.
- SARAH: Right.

06:38.816 --> 06:42.528
And then Susan Duncan can take her place
at the head of Neolution again.

06:46.657 --> 06:49.160
Evie is hunting you, Sarah.

06:49.994 --> 06:51.788
We both need her gone.

06:51.871 --> 06:53.664
I have... (STAMMERS)

06:55.792 --> 06:56.834
Mmm.

06:56.959 --> 07:01.839
...my limitations, but Ira will help.

07:03.341 --> 07:06.636
We do this,
it's with our people, our way.

07:08.221 --> 07:09.680
Give me the file.

07:11.390 --> 07:13.351
We'll let you know how it goes.

07:22.318 --> 07:24.487
(BABY WAILING)

07:26.072 --> 07:27.657
DOCTOR: <i>Okay.</i>

07:27.740 --> 07:30.701
<i>- She's gone.</i>
- EVIE: Oh, no.

07:30.827 --> 07:31.869
DR. VAN LIER: I'm sorry.

07:31.994 --> 07:33.830
It came for you this morning.

07:34.539 --> 07:36.958
"Leave us alone,
or the whole video goes online."

07:37.041 --> 07:38.401
Like I'm going to let that happen.

07:39.710 --> 07:41.212
They could ruin everything.

07:41.337 --> 07:43.589
- Why haven't we found them?
- We are working on it.

07:43.714 --> 07:45.258
Traced the email to a fixed address,

07:45.383 --> 07:47.927
but the less you know
about that, the better.

07:48.052 --> 07:49.846
And what should I know
about Detective Duko?

07:51.347 --> 07:52.849
He disappeared tailing Sarah.

07:52.932 --> 07:56.602
Evie, you need to focus
on the press conference tonight.

07:56.727 --> 07:58.062
Let us handle this.

08:02.275 --> 08:04.026
I have jobs for each of you.

08:12.410 --> 08:14.412
- Honey!
- Oh, Donnie, thank God!

08:14.537 --> 08:16.664
Oh, my God, it is so good to see you.

08:16.747 --> 08:17.999
Oh, Donnie! Donnie, please.

08:18.082 --> 08:19.393
I just...
I never thought I'd see you again.

08:19.417 --> 08:21.097
- Let's just go home...
- Contain yourself.

08:21.210 --> 08:23.504
Adele is coming over
to talk about your defense, okay?

08:23.588 --> 08:26.048
Well, she can wait!
Daddy needs his conjugal, baby.

08:26.132 --> 08:27.550
Donnie, our lives are imploding

08:27.633 --> 08:29.468
and all you can think about
is your stiffy?

08:29.594 --> 08:31.929
You're right. I'm sorry.

08:32.054 --> 08:33.764
You've been such a rock.

08:33.890 --> 08:35.474
How are the kids doing in Florida?

08:35.600 --> 08:37.768
Oh, they're safe, except for my mother.

08:37.894 --> 08:40.813
Yeah? What about you?
How's the musical?

08:40.938 --> 08:42.356
It's a fraud.

08:42.440 --> 08:43.876
We're singing <i>Jesus Christ Superstar,</i>

08:43.900 --> 08:46.110
and I've completely lost touch
with my faith.

08:46.235 --> 08:48.196
- No, you haven't.
- Yes, I have!

08:48.279 --> 08:50.781
I'm Judas,
and I can't even pray anymore.

08:50.907 --> 08:53.576
- Well, listen.
- Oh! Donnie! Oh.

08:53.659 --> 08:55.244
Come on. Let's just go home, all right?

08:55.328 --> 08:58.581
We will let Adele
get us out of this first,

08:58.664 --> 09:00.958
and then I'll make you
see God, Ms. Hendrix.

09:01.083 --> 09:02.418
- Donnie!
- Mmm-hmm.

09:02.501 --> 09:03.836
(CHUCKLES)

09:03.961 --> 09:05.504
- Here, hold my undies.
- Oh, God!

09:05.630 --> 09:06.964
- They're dirty!
- Are they...

09:07.798 --> 09:11.093
Kendra and Tabitha were both full term.

09:11.177 --> 09:13.054
Kendra's got a four-year-old son.

09:13.137 --> 09:14.740
- All right, you're a single mom...
- (CELL PHONE CHIMES)

09:14.764 --> 09:16.992
...and desperate enough
to surrogate a monster for money.

09:17.016 --> 09:18.976
- How far can you run?
- ART: Yeah...

09:19.894 --> 09:21.938
Tender mercies, Donnie's out of remand.

09:22.813 --> 09:23.814
(SOFTLY) God.

09:23.940 --> 09:27.276
Hendrix is on bail,
Cosima's on the Island of Dr. Moreau

09:27.360 --> 09:29.987
and Helena is AWOL.

09:30.112 --> 09:32.841
I'm meant to be bringing us together,
and we're falling apart. (SIGHS)

09:32.865 --> 09:35.701
- Well, at least you still got Rachel.
- Oh, God, yeah.

09:35.826 --> 09:37.495
All right, I gotta go.

09:37.620 --> 09:40.957
I gotta go make sure the Hendrixes
don't let my bio-sister into Clone Club.

09:41.040 --> 09:43.542
- Love you.
- I know. You, too.

09:43.668 --> 09:46.212
- (DOOR SLIDING)
- You got something?

09:46.337 --> 09:48.631
Uh, maybe.
Description matches two women

09:48.714 --> 09:51.342
checked into the
Centertown Shelter yesterday.

09:51.467 --> 09:54.220
One pregnant, the other with a newborn.

09:56.514 --> 09:58.015
(BIRDS CHIRPING)

09:59.225 --> 10:00.351
SUSAN: Good.

10:01.185 --> 10:05.064
Now prick the oocyte right in the center
to avoid trauma.

10:05.189 --> 10:06.941
I don't want to screw this up.

10:07.024 --> 10:08.067
Relax.

10:08.192 --> 10:11.862
You're merely
fertilizing LEDA with CASTOR.

10:11.988 --> 10:13.322
(COSIMA CHUCKLES)

10:15.032 --> 10:16.200
Good.

10:16.325 --> 10:19.578
Now draw up some plasma
so we know the membrane is ruptured

10:20.329 --> 10:22.331
and drop it back in the center.

10:25.418 --> 10:29.880
And we are on our way
to compatible stem cells,

10:30.548 --> 10:32.508
thanks to
Sarah and Ira's contributions.

10:32.591 --> 10:33.634
(SIGHS)

10:33.718 --> 10:35.177
You all right?

10:36.554 --> 10:40.725
Yeah, I think the trip up here yesterday
took it out of me a little.

10:43.060 --> 10:45.646
I will put our egg in a culture.

10:45.730 --> 10:47.565
Why don't you lie down for a bit?

10:48.524 --> 10:49.567
Mmm.

10:50.735 --> 10:52.903
I have brought you some reading.

10:54.905 --> 10:56.490
No way.

10:56.574 --> 10:58.367
It's very rare.

10:59.368 --> 11:01.329
<i>"On the Science of Neolution.</i>

11:01.412 --> 11:03.414
"P.T. Westmorland."

11:09.128 --> 11:10.379
SARAH: Oh, no.

11:11.255 --> 11:13.424
ART: Yeah...
Centertown Women's Shelter.

11:14.425 --> 11:15.676
This doesn't look good.

11:15.760 --> 11:18.387
Shit. No, no, no. You stay right here.

11:19.055 --> 11:21.098
You're not Beth Childs today.

11:22.558 --> 11:24.268
All right, fine.

11:28.564 --> 11:30.274
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

11:34.904 --> 11:36.989
I... I just talked to her.

11:37.114 --> 11:38.949
It doesn't make any sense.

11:39.075 --> 11:40.785
She told me to meet her here.

11:40.910 --> 11:42.328
No, I'm hearing you.

11:42.453 --> 11:44.789
But you have to let us do our job now.

11:45.456 --> 11:46.999
I saw cruisers. What's going on?

11:47.124 --> 11:48.667
In here.

11:48.793 --> 11:50.795
Looks like we have a suicide.

11:51.796 --> 11:53.172
So no signs of foul play?

11:53.297 --> 11:56.175
No, not that I can see.
Forensics is on the way.

11:57.176 --> 11:59.720
Though she checked in
with a girl named Kendra,

11:59.804 --> 12:01.097
but now we can't find her.

12:01.180 --> 12:02.681
(CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING)

12:04.600 --> 12:06.685
- (SOFTLY) Jesus.
- Yeah.

12:06.811 --> 12:09.814
Her other friend out there
found her hanging from that pipe.

12:09.939 --> 12:12.525
No vital signs for her or the baby.

12:18.322 --> 12:20.157
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

12:21.867 --> 12:23.953
Oh, shit. Helena!

12:24.036 --> 12:25.746
HELENA: <i>Hello,</i> sestra.

12:25.830 --> 12:27.748
(STAMMERS) Hey,
we've been worried about you.

12:27.832 --> 12:29.472
Why haven't you answered
your clone phone?

12:29.542 --> 12:31.794
I think ringing is broken.

12:31.877 --> 12:34.380
<i>- Okay, where are you?</i>
- (SNIFFS)

12:36.132 --> 12:38.175
I have a place of my own now.

12:39.218 --> 12:40.719
How is Kira?

12:40.845 --> 12:43.305
<i>She's getting bigger.</i>

12:43.389 --> 12:45.307
How about you? How are yours?

12:45.391 --> 12:47.810
Yes, much kicking.

12:47.893 --> 12:49.520
They're fighting like us.

12:49.645 --> 12:50.855
<i>- Yeah?</i>
- (CHUCKLES)

12:50.980 --> 12:52.356
<i>I'm happy for you.</i>

12:52.481 --> 12:54.775
<i>Glad you're far away from all this.</i>

12:54.859 --> 12:56.277
Why? Is problem?

12:56.360 --> 12:58.195
No, no, no.

12:59.196 --> 13:02.533
- Is problem with family Hendrick?
<i>- No, look...</i>

13:02.658 --> 13:04.452
It's nothing for you to worry about.

13:04.535 --> 13:06.412
It's just the usual shit.

13:08.581 --> 13:10.207
Oh, I've gotta go.

13:10.875 --> 13:14.295
<i>You keep those babies safe. All right?</i>

13:14.378 --> 13:16.046
<i>Say yes.</i>

13:16.922 --> 13:18.007
Okay.

13:18.591 --> 13:20.926
Okay. Bye, meathead.

13:21.051 --> 13:23.929
Er... (CLEARS THROAT) Trina?

13:24.054 --> 13:25.222
Beth!

13:26.390 --> 13:27.808
Why are you dressed like that?

13:27.892 --> 13:31.896
Er, I'm undercover.
I'm, er, plainclothes.

13:33.439 --> 13:34.982
What's wrong?

13:35.065 --> 13:36.400
You were right about Brightborn.

13:37.234 --> 13:39.278
It's way worse than I thought.

13:40.738 --> 13:42.907
These wounds look to be defensive.

13:43.908 --> 13:45.117
Could be.

13:45.242 --> 13:46.911
You seen Marty Duko lately?

13:49.079 --> 13:51.499
- No, why?
- Guy blew his shift.

13:51.582 --> 13:53.250
Nobody knows where he is.

13:56.086 --> 13:58.088
No, I haven't seen him.

13:58.923 --> 14:00.758
Hope he's okay.

14:05.596 --> 14:08.516
TRINA: <i>Tabitha called me
as soon as they broke out.</i>

14:08.599 --> 14:10.601
Scared shitless.

14:10.726 --> 14:11.894
It wasn't a suicide.

14:11.977 --> 14:13.771
- No way.
- I believe you.

14:14.605 --> 14:18.484
- But, erm, what about Kendra Dupree?
- Oh, my God.

14:18.609 --> 14:19.818
I hope she got away.

14:20.736 --> 14:23.656
- Where would she go?
- I already told the detective in there.

14:24.406 --> 14:27.243
Okay, that's good, but I... (STAMMERS)

14:27.326 --> 14:28.966
Can you tell me?
I feel like I could help.

14:30.621 --> 14:33.666
Kendra talked about, er,
an empty house somewhere.

14:33.791 --> 14:36.210
(SNIFFLES) A friend
of her family who died.

14:36.293 --> 14:39.380
Something Steinbeck. Clara? Mary?

14:39.463 --> 14:40.506
Any idea where?

14:40.631 --> 14:41.983
I just know that
the house wouldn't sell,

14:42.007 --> 14:44.093
because the town's economy is so crap.

14:45.177 --> 14:46.220
Tisdale?

14:46.303 --> 14:49.306
That would make sense.
Kendra's from there.

14:50.641 --> 14:52.434
You gotta find her before they do.

14:52.518 --> 14:55.354
Yeah, okay. We will.

14:58.774 --> 15:00.317
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

15:04.280 --> 15:05.281
Detective.

15:05.364 --> 15:07.241
I'm at the scene.

15:07.324 --> 15:09.159
The one that got away, Kendra Dupree,

15:09.285 --> 15:11.954
<i>I got a little tip
she's headed to Tisdale.</i>

15:12.705 --> 15:14.790
But you're not the only ones
looking for her.

15:22.006 --> 15:23.299
(ADELE SIGHS)

15:23.382 --> 15:25.634
Okay, could be worse.

15:25.718 --> 15:28.887
Er, they've charged you with
possession, trafficking and importing.

15:29.013 --> 15:31.140
Importing? No, no, we weren't importing.

15:31.223 --> 15:32.891
Shh. Er, what is their evidence?

15:33.017 --> 15:34.577
Er, we won't know
for a couple of weeks.

15:34.643 --> 15:37.813
Until then, just comply
with your bail conditions

15:37.896 --> 15:39.648
and try not to worry.

15:39.732 --> 15:40.858
- Okay.
- Okay.

15:40.983 --> 15:43.611
FYI, there's two plainclothes

15:43.694 --> 15:45.946
parked outside your house
in an unmarked car.

15:46.030 --> 15:47.790
- We're under surveillance?
- FELIX: Mmm-hmm.

15:47.865 --> 15:50.159
Is that normal?
We've already been charged.

15:50.242 --> 15:52.911
Seems like Detective Duko
has quite a hard-on for y'all.

15:53.037 --> 15:54.538
(STAMMERS) It's not him.

15:56.248 --> 15:57.916
Why couldn't it be him?

16:01.045 --> 16:02.421
'Cause he's on leave.

16:02.546 --> 16:04.548
Okay, how would you know
if he's on leave?

16:04.673 --> 16:07.176
You know what?
Maybe we should review the scope of

16:07.259 --> 16:08.844
- lawyer-client privilege again.
- Mmm.

16:08.927 --> 16:11.055
Okay, is something going on
with Detective Duko?

16:14.433 --> 16:15.476
(SMACKS LIPS) No.

16:15.559 --> 16:17.061
- No.
- No, I don't think there is.

16:17.186 --> 16:19.897
Great! Erm, we can continue
this conversation at home.

16:20.022 --> 16:21.207
Let's maybe have a drink there.

16:21.231 --> 16:23.567
- We'll leave you two.
- BOTH: Bye!

16:26.862 --> 16:28.197
(CHUCKLES)

16:28.280 --> 16:31.742
It's functioning perfectly, Evie.
The therapy's underway.

16:31.867 --> 16:34.578
- Well, I won't miss the shingles.
- (CHUCKLES)

16:34.703 --> 16:38.374
(SIGHS) Just promise me
that you'll find that carrier, Ian,

16:38.457 --> 16:40.918
- or none of it will matter.
- I promise.

16:46.757 --> 16:48.276
ART: What do you
know about this place?

16:48.300 --> 16:49.426
SARAH: Tisdale? Nothing.

16:49.551 --> 16:51.220
I mean, it looks rough.

16:51.303 --> 16:53.097
I'm guessing Brightborn
offered Kendra money

16:53.222 --> 16:54.807
and she thought, "How bad can it be?"

16:54.932 --> 16:55.974
ART: Pretty bad.

16:59.103 --> 17:00.104
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

17:00.187 --> 17:01.247
So, how many more Steinbecks
we got left?

17:01.271 --> 17:04.108
Er, two. And one Steinbock.

17:05.067 --> 17:07.194
Rachel, I told you I'd call you.

17:07.277 --> 17:08.278
Yes, an hour ago.

17:08.404 --> 17:10.698
<i>Well, we're still looking
for Kendra Dupree.</i>

17:10.781 --> 17:12.950
Well, we have new information
that could help.

17:13.075 --> 17:17.621
Kendra took her four-year-old son
William to friends in Pickering.

17:17.746 --> 17:18.747
I'll send the address.

17:18.830 --> 17:20.915
<i>No, we've got our own leads out here.</i>

17:21.791 --> 17:24.127
Where are you, then? How can we help?

17:24.252 --> 17:26.255
If I need help, I'll ask.

17:30.134 --> 17:31.218
(CELL PHONE BEEPS)

17:31.301 --> 17:33.178
You really don't like each other,
do you?

17:33.303 --> 17:35.514
She put a pencil in my brain.

17:38.183 --> 17:39.810
(PROCESSING)

17:41.353 --> 17:42.479
IRA: Okay.

17:42.604 --> 17:45.691
We have the location
of Sarah's last phone call.

17:45.816 --> 17:47.317
She's in Tisdale.

17:48.026 --> 17:49.153
You should go, then.

17:50.320 --> 17:53.115
Contingency, in case she falters.

17:59.997 --> 18:01.874
You're the sick one.

18:03.041 --> 18:04.293
Cosima.

18:06.628 --> 18:07.921
You're the sick one, too, right?

18:08.005 --> 18:09.423
Charlotte?

18:09.506 --> 18:11.258
I don't feel very sick yet.

18:11.341 --> 18:12.551
That's good.

18:13.552 --> 18:16.013
How do you brush your hair?

18:16.138 --> 18:17.681
I don't.

18:17.806 --> 18:19.516
Just wake up and it looks like this.

18:20.476 --> 18:22.186
You wanna feel?

18:24.021 --> 18:26.523
- I used to have pigtails, too.
- Do you like the book?

18:28.192 --> 18:29.318
Yep.

18:29.985 --> 18:32.946
But I'm finding it
a bit overwhelming right now.

18:33.030 --> 18:35.115
I didn't even know that this guy,

18:35.199 --> 18:38.243
P.T. Westmorland,
was involved in Neolution.

18:38.368 --> 18:39.703
This is my favorite part.

18:42.790 --> 18:44.184
COSIMA: Is this
the island that we're on?

18:44.208 --> 18:46.794
CHARLOTTE: It's made
out of Precambrian rock,

18:46.877 --> 18:48.420
almost four billion years old.

18:49.713 --> 18:50.756
We're at this end.

18:52.674 --> 18:55.552
You're right. That is a very cool part.

18:57.262 --> 19:00.057
ADELE: First,
your foster sister does a test on us,

19:00.182 --> 19:03.060
like she's got geneticists
at her disposal,

19:03.185 --> 19:06.271
and then I meet her suburbanite
twin sister, the drug dealer.

19:07.439 --> 19:09.024
And her husband gets thrown in jail,

19:09.107 --> 19:10.901
and the cops just
throw the book at him.

19:11.902 --> 19:13.987
Did your family
threaten Duko or something?

19:14.071 --> 19:16.490
Adele, you're making it sound
like we're the mob.

19:16.573 --> 19:17.717
What? So I'm reading this wrong?

19:17.741 --> 19:20.661
Well, you did just mix
mood stabilizers with gin, darling.

19:20.744 --> 19:22.079
That's brunch.

19:24.915 --> 19:26.041
Hello, Felix.

19:27.292 --> 19:29.002
FELIX: Hey, Helena!

19:29.086 --> 19:32.047
Hi! Adele, Helena.
Helena, this is Adele.

19:32.130 --> 19:34.007
This is my half sister.

19:34.091 --> 19:35.133
What?

19:35.259 --> 19:37.302
Different mother, same father.

19:37.427 --> 19:41.306
So you must be Sarah's other sister.

19:43.267 --> 19:45.644
Yes. Same mother,

19:45.769 --> 19:46.770
womb.

19:47.604 --> 19:50.399
- So it's triplets now, huh?
- Yeah.

19:50.482 --> 19:52.526
- Yeah, yeah.
- From different regions.

19:52.609 --> 19:54.152
- From the same stomach.
- FELIX: Yeah.

19:54.278 --> 19:55.838
Countries in there?
Different countries?

19:57.072 --> 19:58.992
- This is... I should go.
- That's probably best.

19:59.116 --> 20:01.159
Nonsense, I think you should stay.

20:01.285 --> 20:04.246
I have so many questions for ya.

20:05.122 --> 20:06.957
All starting with
where you got that hat.

20:07.624 --> 20:09.167
Have you named it yet?

20:13.630 --> 20:14.798
(BOTH GRUNTING)

20:14.923 --> 20:16.967
Oh, God! Oh, God!

20:17.092 --> 20:18.343
Can you use a different word?

20:18.468 --> 20:21.138
- Just... Just call me a bad man.
- Oh, you're a bad man.

20:21.263 --> 20:23.891
- I'm a bad man who runs this cell block!
- Oh, you run it.

20:23.974 --> 20:25.660
- I run this cell block!
- Yeah, you run it.

20:25.684 --> 20:27.269
Oh, honey, I love you.

20:27.352 --> 20:29.146
(MOANING)

20:29.271 --> 20:30.814
- (ALISON PANTS)
- DONNIE: Oh.

20:32.190 --> 20:33.984
- Oh!
- (SIGHS)

20:34.109 --> 20:37.404
Donnie, would you pray with me, please?

20:37.487 --> 20:39.740
- Right now?
- Yes, yes.

20:39.823 --> 20:42.618
(SOFTLY) Just close your eyes.
Close them.

20:44.995 --> 20:47.497
(SIGHING) Oh, dear Lord...

20:48.665 --> 20:52.502
(SIGHS) I know we haven't been
very good Christians lately,

20:53.503 --> 20:57.549
but we are very grateful
that Donnie's out of remand,

20:57.674 --> 21:00.218
and we're trying our best to be good...

21:01.511 --> 21:02.971
To be good.

21:03.889 --> 21:06.016
Oh, crap. I'm... I can't do this.

21:06.683 --> 21:08.977
Oh, God's forsaken me.

21:09.061 --> 21:11.480
Honey... (STAMMERS)
I'm sure he gets the point.

21:11.563 --> 21:12.731
No, no.

21:13.398 --> 21:15.567
Everybody knows we're criminals.

21:15.692 --> 21:17.653
They stare at me in the grocery store.

21:17.736 --> 21:19.780
And there are cops
outside of our house, Donnie.

21:19.863 --> 21:21.323
We have to get out of here.

21:21.406 --> 21:22.699
Honey, we can't.

21:22.824 --> 21:24.944
I forfeited my passport
as part of my bail conditions.

21:27.162 --> 21:28.830
(SIGHS) Well, we'll...

21:28.914 --> 21:31.708
We'll go to Niagara,
and we'll pretend it's a holiday.

21:31.833 --> 21:33.919
We'll send for the kids,
and we'll go hide

21:34.002 --> 21:36.213
in one of those waterpark hotels.

21:36.338 --> 21:37.881
The last time we went to Splashdown,

21:37.965 --> 21:39.508
Oscar got foot and mouth disease.

21:39.591 --> 21:41.802
Donnie, would you
work with me here, please?

21:41.885 --> 21:43.220
Er, yeah.

21:43.345 --> 21:46.056
- Let's go to Niagara.
- Good.

22:38.233 --> 22:40.393
ART: All right,
this is the last Steinbeck on the list.

22:43.822 --> 22:45.115
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

22:47.159 --> 22:48.618
There's baby stuff.

22:49.828 --> 22:51.496
(DOORBELL RINGING)

23:02.507 --> 23:04.092
Just do it quick.

23:14.686 --> 23:16.021
(DOOR CLOSES)

23:16.146 --> 23:17.189
Hello?

23:19.024 --> 23:20.150
Kendra?

23:30.827 --> 23:31.828
(BABY CRYING)

23:36.500 --> 23:38.794
ART: Kendra Dupree?

23:38.877 --> 23:40.837
(BABY CONTINUES CRYING)

23:52.682 --> 23:53.850
(SOFTLY) Hi.

23:54.643 --> 23:56.311
I won't let you hurt my baby.

24:01.191 --> 24:03.360
(BREATH TREMBLING) Get away from him.

24:03.485 --> 24:04.569
We're not from Brightborn.

24:04.694 --> 24:07.155
- We... We don't want to hurt your kid.
- I don't believe you.

24:07.239 --> 24:09.324
Listen very carefully.
I'm a police officer,

24:09.407 --> 24:12.744
I'm going to reach into my pocket
real slow and show you my ID.

24:13.870 --> 24:14.913
There you go.

24:16.373 --> 24:18.416
- All right? Just put down the gun.
- Move.

24:18.542 --> 24:19.668
Okay, okay.

24:19.751 --> 24:21.128
(BABY CRYING)

24:21.211 --> 24:22.587
(SHUSHING)

24:33.390 --> 24:34.558
(SOFTLY) It's okay.

24:36.560 --> 24:37.602
It's okay.

24:38.562 --> 24:41.231
It's okay, it's okay, it's okay.

24:43.400 --> 24:48.947
See, Felix neglected to tell me twice
that Sarah's got sisters.

24:49.072 --> 24:53.076
Oh, and you're so preggo and foreign.

24:53.201 --> 24:55.495
Because it wasn't pertinent
and I'm not a gossip.

24:55.579 --> 24:57.164
Oh, you're not a gossip.
(SCOFFS) Right.

24:57.247 --> 24:58.290
Where is Sarah?

24:59.124 --> 25:01.269
She's good. Good, darling.
She's just busy. Busy, busy.

25:01.293 --> 25:03.712
- Alison? Donnie Hendrick?
- Yeah, they're great.

25:03.795 --> 25:06.381
- All great. Totally fine.
- Oh, yeah, they're doing real well,

25:06.464 --> 25:09.184
aside from the fact that they're
currently under federal prosecution.

25:09.259 --> 25:11.219
FELIX: Adele!
ADELE: What? Shouldn't she know?

25:11.303 --> 25:13.388
- They are sisters.
- What does this mean? Jail?

25:13.471 --> 25:14.681
No, no.

25:14.764 --> 25:17.100
Well, maybe Donnie. Yes. I don't know.

25:17.225 --> 25:18.268
Because of Pouchy?

25:20.437 --> 25:21.855
So she knows about the killings?

25:21.938 --> 25:23.732
(LAUGHS)

25:23.815 --> 25:27.986
Tangential, of course... (STAMMERS)
To drugs and missing cops.

25:28.111 --> 25:29.571
You have a loud voice.

25:29.654 --> 25:32.032
Yes, I do, because,
see, my brother here,

25:32.115 --> 25:34.201
he's got more secrets than a freemason,

25:34.284 --> 25:36.828
and I'm getting real tired
of sifting through all his bullshit.

25:36.953 --> 25:38.830
Maybe bullshit is where you belong.

25:39.748 --> 25:41.750
Did you just step up to me,
little triplet?

25:42.250 --> 25:43.835
- (SNARLS)
- Jesus!

25:43.960 --> 25:46.040
Okay, whoa! No, you don't
want to do that, all right?

25:46.796 --> 25:47.797
It's okay.

25:47.923 --> 25:49.925
We don't need to do
any of that, all right?

25:50.008 --> 25:51.259
All good.

25:51.760 --> 25:55.430
Erm, <i>sestra,</i> you give me
an hour here with Adele,

25:55.513 --> 25:58.558
and then I promise we are
going to catch up right proper, okay?

25:58.642 --> 25:59.809
(HELENA SIGHS)

26:01.144 --> 26:02.479
You are safe?

26:02.604 --> 26:04.522
Yeah, hope so.

26:07.484 --> 26:09.194
(DOOR SLIDING)

26:13.323 --> 26:16.785
Wow. She was something else.

26:16.868 --> 26:19.955
(SNIFFLES) And I don't think that hat
was store-bought, neither.

26:20.038 --> 26:22.290
You're gonna sober up,
and then you're gonna go.

26:24.876 --> 26:27.462
I'm not leaving without an explanation.

26:29.673 --> 26:35.387
Adele, you are so
beautifully unsullied by all this shit.

26:36.513 --> 26:39.474
And I'm not going to be the person
that ruins that for you.

26:42.519 --> 26:43.645
Okay, okay.

26:44.396 --> 26:45.480
(SNIFFLES)

26:46.690 --> 26:49.025
Genetics doesn't really
make a family, does it?

26:50.360 --> 26:51.987
- No.
- Honesty and...

26:52.070 --> 26:55.115
(SNIFFLES) And, er, acceptance?

26:55.198 --> 26:56.866
That's what it's all about, hey?

26:58.910 --> 27:00.954
(SOFTLY) This is my life.
I'm really sorry.

27:01.037 --> 27:02.080
Okay.

27:02.706 --> 27:04.124
Mmm. Okay.

27:04.207 --> 27:08.378
Erm, I'm gonna leave you
with your real family for a while.

27:08.503 --> 27:09.546
(ADELE SNIFFLES)

27:10.505 --> 27:11.548
(SOFTLY) Okay.

27:22.434 --> 27:24.060
(BABY COOING)

27:25.228 --> 27:28.231
- How did you find me?
- SARAH: We spoke to Trina.

27:28.356 --> 27:30.442
Erm, I knew her from before.

27:31.526 --> 27:33.445
I was just coming back with lunch.

27:34.738 --> 27:36.364
They killed Tabitha, didn't they?

27:36.948 --> 27:39.868
Well, if they did,
they made it look like a suicide.

27:39.951 --> 27:42.203
SARAH: We know about Brightborn.

27:42.287 --> 27:44.080
You want to tell us what happened?

27:44.205 --> 27:46.166
- (BABY CRIES)
- (SHUSHING)

27:46.249 --> 27:47.625
(BABY COUGHING)

27:47.751 --> 27:49.419
(SOFTLY) Shh. It's okay.

27:50.420 --> 27:53.298
Tabitha and I were nearing full term.

27:54.090 --> 27:58.136
We heard rumors some of the babies
were born... Different.

27:59.095 --> 28:01.014
One night, the nurse fell asleep,

28:01.097 --> 28:02.724
so we snuck out of the ward.

28:03.641 --> 28:05.935
We heard a baby crying,

28:06.061 --> 28:09.147
saw two doctors sneak into
an operating room...

28:12.233 --> 28:16.404
(BREATHES HEAVILY)
I'd snuck this phone in to call my son.

28:18.573 --> 28:19.699
(BABY CRYING)

28:19.783 --> 28:20.950
(SHUSHING)

28:21.785 --> 28:23.453
DOCTOR: (ON RECORDING)
<i>See this dysplasia?</i>

28:23.578 --> 28:26.122
<i>Must be excruciating. Hold her steady.</i>

28:26.998 --> 28:28.416
(BABY CONTINUES CRYING)

28:33.630 --> 28:36.591
<i>Just a little bee sting,
and then you won't feel anything at all.</i>

28:38.426 --> 28:40.011
(BABY WAILING)

28:40.136 --> 28:41.930
(ECG MONITOR BEEPING)

28:43.348 --> 28:44.474
<i>Okay.</i>

28:44.599 --> 28:45.683
(ECG MONITOR FLATLINES)

28:45.809 --> 28:47.018
<i>She's gone.</i>

28:52.357 --> 28:53.942
The next day we ran.

28:55.151 --> 28:56.820
I named him Jacob.

28:57.987 --> 28:59.948
They put this beautiful baby in me,

29:00.865 --> 29:02.158
but he was born blind.

29:02.283 --> 29:03.284
(COOS)

29:03.368 --> 29:06.287
If they find him,
they'll put him down, too.

29:06.830 --> 29:08.331
(STAMMERS)

29:08.456 --> 29:10.291
If you're willing to
come forward with this,

29:11.209 --> 29:12.585
we could expose them.

29:12.669 --> 29:14.838
We could end all this.

29:14.963 --> 29:16.816
Look, you take the video
and you leave me out of it.

29:16.840 --> 29:18.133
That won't work, Kendra.

29:18.216 --> 29:20.427
Without you,
the video could be discounted.

29:20.510 --> 29:22.011
Look what they did to Tabitha.

29:22.554 --> 29:23.847
I have another son.

29:24.514 --> 29:25.598
They'll hurt us.

29:25.682 --> 29:27.350
I know they will.

29:27.475 --> 29:28.685
(SOFTLY) Hi.

29:39.529 --> 29:40.530
So?

29:42.991 --> 29:45.076
What do you think
of Neolution's forefather?

29:45.201 --> 29:47.287
I think he's fascinating,

29:47.370 --> 29:50.290
for a racist blowhard
who thinks that poverty is genetic.

29:50.373 --> 29:51.458
(SNIFFLES)

29:51.541 --> 29:53.960
Consider the era,
the Victorian mindset.

29:54.043 --> 29:55.187
Is your mindset so different?

29:55.211 --> 29:56.671
(CHUCKLES)

29:56.754 --> 29:58.840
Our ethics debate again.

29:58.923 --> 30:03.678
Well, I just met a little girl
with a deformed leg

30:04.387 --> 30:06.097
and a terminal illness.

30:07.056 --> 30:09.017
When I created Charlotte,

30:09.893 --> 30:12.353
I was under tremendous pressure
to continue LEDA.

30:13.104 --> 30:16.065
I didn't have Kendall's
replicating cell line.

30:16.191 --> 30:17.692
I don't understand. What pressure?

30:17.775 --> 30:18.985
It doesn't matter.

30:19.068 --> 30:20.695
She is a life.

30:21.571 --> 30:23.448
She's unique. She's...

30:23.573 --> 30:25.241
She's happy.

30:25.366 --> 30:27.785
And, hopefully, we will cure her.

30:27.911 --> 30:29.078
(SMACKS LIPS)

30:30.747 --> 30:34.459
The cumulus cells
are starting to strip off the egg.

30:34.584 --> 30:37.086
- (CLEARS THROAT)
- That's excellent news.

30:38.379 --> 30:40.423
Tomorrow, we should have a zygote!

30:45.762 --> 30:47.805
Of course she's reluctant
to come forward.

30:47.889 --> 30:49.265
You have to convince her, Sarah.

30:49.390 --> 30:52.018
I'm trying, but it's not our decision,

30:52.101 --> 30:53.853
- is it? It's hers.
<i>- Listen to me.</i>

30:53.937 --> 30:56.981
If you found her,
Brightborn is right behind.

30:57.106 --> 30:58.608
<i>Tell her we'll protect her.</i>

30:58.733 --> 31:01.653
What if we can't? I'm not lying to her.

31:01.778 --> 31:02.904
Then let me.

31:02.987 --> 31:05.823
Or use the information
I gave you about her other son.

31:06.324 --> 31:09.160
(SIGHS) I'm not
blackmailing her, Rachel.

31:09.285 --> 31:12.622
(SIGHS) <i>Oh, Sarah, don't be naive.
We have one chance at...</i>

31:16.334 --> 31:17.585
(SIGHS)

31:20.171 --> 31:22.298
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

31:22.966 --> 31:25.176
- Still here.
- RACHEL: <i>Sarah won't act.</i>

31:25.301 --> 31:27.470
We need that contingency plan.

31:28.263 --> 31:31.349
All right, but there's a complication.

31:37.480 --> 31:39.816
- He's sleeping.
- SARAH: All right.

31:39.941 --> 31:41.192
We're not safe here.

31:41.317 --> 31:43.695
We need, er...
We need you to come with us.

31:43.820 --> 31:45.113
Like protective custody?

31:46.155 --> 31:49.701
Honestly, there are police
that we can't trust.

31:49.826 --> 31:52.412
But we've got a safe house,
and it's very well protected.

31:52.495 --> 31:53.580
This is crazy.

31:53.663 --> 31:55.164
I don't even know you people.

31:55.290 --> 31:56.916
Brightborn is after us, too.

31:57.000 --> 31:59.335
And we both have daughters,

31:59.460 --> 32:02.880
and we put them first every day,
just like you're doing with Jacob.

32:03.673 --> 32:05.425
But we need you to help us end this.

32:05.508 --> 32:07.719
Could you go get him, please?

32:09.012 --> 32:10.054
Okay.

32:12.181 --> 32:13.683
ART: (SHUSHING SOFTLY) Quiet.

32:15.518 --> 32:17.979
- They're outside.
- (BABY WAILING)

32:18.062 --> 32:19.397
(KENDRA GASPS)

32:20.023 --> 32:22.025
- Kendra!
- ART: Let her go, let her go.

32:22.150 --> 32:23.651
She'll keep him quiet.

32:28.865 --> 32:31.200
- (PHONE RINGING)
- Whose phone is that?

32:32.910 --> 32:34.037
Landline.

32:34.162 --> 32:36.164
- Whoa.
- Shit.

32:39.375 --> 32:42.545
- (SHUSHING)
- (PHONE CONTINUES RINGING)

32:44.422 --> 32:46.716
- Hello?
- RACHEL: <i>Kendra Dupree?</i>

32:46.841 --> 32:48.551
Listen to me carefully.

32:48.676 --> 32:52.347
<i>I have an associate waiting for you
in a car outside.</i>

32:52.430 --> 32:53.973
<i>I know Sarah is there.</i>

32:54.057 --> 32:58.269
I also know your son, William,
is with Carrie Munroe,

32:58.394 --> 33:00.938
<i>14 Emerson Drive, Pickering.</i>

33:01.064 --> 33:04.400
If you do as I say, he won't be hurt.

33:07.028 --> 33:08.363
(SHUSHING)

33:29.217 --> 33:31.719
- (GUN COCKS)
- Don't move! Police!

33:31.803 --> 33:33.930
Drop your weapons, nice and slow.

33:35.640 --> 33:37.266
Kick 'em over to me!

33:38.768 --> 33:39.936
Get on your knees!

33:40.937 --> 33:42.438
Put your hands behind your heads.

33:43.106 --> 33:44.774
Lock your fingers!

33:45.983 --> 33:48.736
You again? Where's your usual partner?

33:48.820 --> 33:50.780
Why? Do you miss him?

33:51.406 --> 33:53.741
You go get Kendra.
I'll take care of these guys.

33:54.617 --> 33:55.952
(HANDCUFFS CLINKING)

34:00.623 --> 34:01.999
Kendra?

34:04.127 --> 34:05.461
(ENGINE STARTING)

34:05.586 --> 34:07.922
Ira, Stop! Kendra!

34:08.005 --> 34:09.297
(TIRES SCREECHING)

34:14.637 --> 34:15.638
ART: What happened?

34:15.763 --> 34:17.348
She's gone with Ira.

34:17.473 --> 34:19.851
Rachel's screwing us. I'm so stupid.

34:19.976 --> 34:23.312
Did you kill that woman at the shelter?
Hey? Hey?

34:23.438 --> 34:25.815
Oh, no, no! Hey! We're not doing this.

34:27.315 --> 34:29.735
We're going to drop them off
at the precinct.

34:29.819 --> 34:31.487
We'll be out by morning.

34:32.530 --> 34:34.322
- Yeah?
- (SARAH SCOFFS)

34:35.658 --> 34:37.994
Well, I'll be real interested
to see who springs you.

34:39.495 --> 34:44.542
Swimsuits, a hair dryer
and earplugs for your snoring.

34:44.667 --> 34:47.795
Er, I grabbed some Imodium
in case you want that crab salad again.

34:49.297 --> 34:50.339
(SIGHS)

34:51.340 --> 34:53.009
- Hey, the cops are gone.
- Oh.

34:53.134 --> 34:55.636
There's just an ambulance
parked there now.

34:55.719 --> 34:57.805
- Good. Good time to skedaddle.
- Yep.

34:57.889 --> 35:00.183
Let's get out of here...
Wait! Flip flops.

35:00.308 --> 35:03.019
- Er, basement. Basement.
- Right. Okay, okay, okay.

35:17.867 --> 35:19.076
(BANGING)

35:20.203 --> 35:21.370
Donnie?

35:24.874 --> 35:26.375
Donnie?

35:28.878 --> 35:30.087
Donnie.

35:32.757 --> 35:34.592
Oh, Lord! (GASPS)

35:34.717 --> 35:38.012
Sorry to barge in.
We're going to have a little chat.

35:38.095 --> 35:39.472
(SOFTLY) Okay.

35:40.640 --> 35:44.018
Large-scale clinical trials
are just the beginning.

35:44.101 --> 35:47.146
Soon, Brightborn will offer
advanced gene therapy

35:47.230 --> 35:49.440
directly to you and your families.

35:49.565 --> 35:53.569
I can think of no better place
to begin this genetic revolution

35:53.694 --> 35:55.822
than in my hometown of Tisdale.

35:55.905 --> 35:57.240
Thank you.

35:59.867 --> 36:01.786
Okay, I'm ready.

36:05.206 --> 36:07.041
- What is it?
- Rachel Duncan is here.

36:07.124 --> 36:08.835
- In the city?
- Downstairs.

36:08.918 --> 36:12.088
She says she has information
about Kendra Dupree.

36:19.220 --> 36:20.888
(MUFFLED GRUNTING)

36:28.104 --> 36:29.480
(ALISON SIGHS)

36:29.605 --> 36:31.482
You're the tough one
in the family, aren't you?

36:32.441 --> 36:34.277
I guess you'd have to be.

36:37.238 --> 36:39.282
This one is first generation.

36:39.907 --> 36:41.534
It's glitchy as hell.

36:42.535 --> 36:43.828
Messed up a lot of people.

36:46.998 --> 36:51.252
I need you to tell me what Sarah
got up to with Detective Duko.

36:51.335 --> 36:53.296
He disappeared tracking her.

36:54.171 --> 36:57.008
By the time I count to ten,
you're going to answer,

36:57.133 --> 36:59.010
or this goes in.

37:01.846 --> 37:03.139
(SOFTLY) I love you, Donnie.

37:04.473 --> 37:05.766
- (ALISON GASPING)
- One...

37:05.850 --> 37:08.895
- Lord, please...
- ...two, three...

37:08.978 --> 37:11.731
...hear my prayer.
I have sinned and sinned.

37:11.814 --> 37:14.734
- ...four, five, six...
- I have turned my back on my community.

37:14.817 --> 37:15.818
I've lost my way.

37:15.943 --> 37:18.905
- Please, forgive my husband.
- ...seven, eight, nine...

37:18.988 --> 37:20.781
- ...ten.
- Protect my children!

37:20.865 --> 37:22.783
And have mercy...

37:28.998 --> 37:30.541
- (CHOKING)
- (GASPING)

37:36.172 --> 37:38.257
(SHUDDERING) Helena.

37:38.341 --> 37:40.509
Where... Where did you come from?

37:40.635 --> 37:42.887
Beavertail National Park.

37:43.888 --> 37:45.473
It was very peaceful.

37:45.556 --> 37:46.641
(PANTING)

37:46.724 --> 37:48.476
(MUFFLED)

37:49.352 --> 37:51.479
Donnie Hendrick,

37:53.189 --> 37:54.982
you look like roast pig.

37:55.066 --> 37:56.692
(MUFFLED MOANING)

38:03.032 --> 38:05.117
Hey, what the hell are you up to?

38:05.201 --> 38:08.412
- Where's Kendra?
- She and her baby are safe.

38:08.537 --> 38:10.831
Did you threaten to hurt her kid?

38:10.915 --> 38:14.335
Hey? You're worse
than bloody Brightborn, mate.

38:14.418 --> 38:16.738
We're just doing what needs to be done.
What you would not.

38:17.546 --> 38:19.006
Where's Rachel?

38:20.007 --> 38:21.467
She's meeting with Evie.

38:21.550 --> 38:23.135
You let her do that?

38:23.219 --> 38:24.261
It's not what you think.

38:24.387 --> 38:26.889
You're stupid, mate.
She is playing you.

38:27.014 --> 38:29.350
Rachel just wants power.
She'll cut us all down.

38:29.433 --> 38:30.893
Including you.

38:31.894 --> 38:33.688
(INDISTINCT CHATTER)

38:42.571 --> 38:44.073
You're supposed to be on the island.

38:44.198 --> 38:45.741
Well, I'm here.

38:45.866 --> 38:48.369
And lucky for you,
I have your solution.

38:50.121 --> 38:51.372
You know where my carrier is?

38:51.455 --> 38:54.709
She's in my custody,
along with her video.

38:55.543 --> 38:57.712
It's abhorrent.

38:57.795 --> 39:00.798
I'm surprised you left
yourself so vulnerable.

39:02.758 --> 39:04.093
So this is a shakedown.

39:05.720 --> 39:08.597
I prefer to think of it
as a negotiation.

39:10.766 --> 39:13.310
Project LEDA is obsolete.
Off the table.

39:13.436 --> 39:15.604
- Fine.
- Same as Susan.

39:16.897 --> 39:18.858
(SIGHS) Agreed.

39:18.941 --> 39:20.860
Her day has passed.

39:20.943 --> 39:24.780
(SCOFFS) Don't tell me
you want Sarah and her sisters spared.

39:25.656 --> 39:28.034
- You don't know me at all, do you?
- Well, then what?

39:28.117 --> 39:31.162
I take great offense to
something you said to me once,

39:32.079 --> 39:35.666
that Neolution would never allow a clone
a position of power.

39:37.084 --> 39:38.669
Today, that changes.

39:38.794 --> 39:40.171
You want a seat at the table.

39:40.296 --> 39:43.466
And in return,
I give you Kendra and her video,

39:43.591 --> 39:45.134
and no one need know

39:45.259 --> 39:49.680
about engineered birth defects
and euthanized newborns.

39:49.805 --> 39:52.349
- The video's on there?
- Yes. There are no copies.

39:52.475 --> 39:55.728
- And what about Kendra Dupree?
- She's in my hotel room.

39:55.811 --> 39:58.814
- And the child is with her?
- Yes, that's right.

40:00.816 --> 40:02.359
Do we have a deal?

40:05.279 --> 40:07.031
Like I have a choice.

40:07.156 --> 40:08.824
One question.

40:09.992 --> 40:11.535
Why euthanasia?

40:12.995 --> 40:14.997
<i>Surely with
Brightborn's resources you...</i>

40:15.122 --> 40:16.499
You're recording this?

40:16.624 --> 40:19.710
And ready to upload it
to every major news network.

40:19.835 --> 40:21.795
RACHEL: <i>...let them live out
their shortened lives.</i>

40:29.178 --> 40:33.182
If even one of these children
were discovered,

40:33.307 --> 40:35.559
decades of science
would have been shelved.

40:35.684 --> 40:39.146
At the end of the day, euthanizing
severely deformed newborns

40:40.022 --> 40:41.899
was the most humane way forward.

40:42.858 --> 40:44.485
Now if you'll excuse me.

40:47.738 --> 40:49.532
Wow, she did it.

40:50.866 --> 40:52.576
Well done.

40:52.701 --> 40:54.453
Welcome.

40:54.537 --> 40:57.540
What if I were to tell you
that in a few short years,

40:57.665 --> 41:00.167
immune deficiencies
could be eradicated?

41:00.251 --> 41:02.128
Cancer cured.

41:02.211 --> 41:06.132
Blood disease, haemophilia,
hereditary blindness,

41:06.215 --> 41:08.175
all in our past.

41:08.259 --> 41:10.019
- Sound far-fetched?
- (CELL PHONE VIBRATING)

41:10.553 --> 41:13.430
Not to me. Because here
at Brightborn Technologies...

41:13.556 --> 41:16.016
<i>...euthanizing
severely deformed newborns</i>

41:16.100 --> 41:17.935
<i>was the most humane way forward.</i>

41:18.060 --> 41:19.913
Today, we are pleased to
announce federal approval...

41:19.937 --> 41:21.737
- (CELL PHONE CHIMING)
<i>- Must be excruciating.</i>

41:21.772 --> 41:24.000
- ...of phase three clinical trials...
<i>- Hold her steady.</i>

41:24.024 --> 41:26.235
...for implantable,
bioengineered gene therapy.

41:26.360 --> 41:28.946
(CELL PHONES CONTINUE
VIBRATING AND CHIMING)

41:32.241 --> 41:34.201
<i>- She's gone.</i>
- These randomized...

41:34.285 --> 41:37.997
Excuse me. Are babies being euthanized
at Brightborn's birthing facility?

41:38.080 --> 41:40.249
Do Brightborn treatments
cause deformation?

41:40.374 --> 41:41.434
What are you talking about?

41:41.458 --> 41:44.187
Well, we have video of you admitting
to euthanizing Brightborn babies.

41:44.211 --> 41:45.211
How do you respond?

41:45.254 --> 41:46.731
Can you confirm that these are
Brightborn doctors?

41:46.755 --> 41:48.382
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

41:50.092 --> 41:51.093
No comment.

41:52.052 --> 41:53.137
No further questions.

41:57.600 --> 41:58.642
Excuse me.

41:58.767 --> 42:00.603
(CLAMORING CONTINUES)

42:17.786 --> 42:18.829
(SIGHS)

42:33.802 --> 42:35.512
IRA: Rachel?

42:39.141 --> 42:40.976
Is it happening again?

42:43.145 --> 42:44.313
What did you see?

42:44.438 --> 42:46.023
(SIGHS)

42:48.442 --> 42:49.818
It isn't a glitch.

42:50.653 --> 42:52.154
It's the island.

42:53.113 --> 42:54.698
There were people there.

42:56.492 --> 42:59.328
Someone's trying
to show me something, Ira.

43:00.955 --> 43:02.414
(FIRE CRACKLING)

43:02.498 --> 43:04.667
(MUSIC PLAYING)

43:15.135 --> 43:17.888
(DOOR OPENING AND CLOSING)

43:18.013 --> 43:20.057
(INDISTINCT RADIO CHATTER)

43:45.666 --> 43:46.917
- (GUNSHOT)
- (GASPS)

43:47.084 --> 43:49.503
KRYSTAL: <i>I have intel
about that French doctor.</i>

43:49.878 --> 43:51.046
Ow!

43:51.213 --> 43:54.258
RACHEL: <i>Controlling evolution,
it's the ultimate power.</i>

43:54.383 --> 43:56.593
COSIMA: <i>You don't even
care about a cure, do you?</i>

43:57.469 --> 43:58.470
No.

43:58.554 --> 44:00.556
SARAH: <i>We don't belong
to anybody, mate!</i>

44:00.723 --> 44:01.932
SUSAN: <i>No, Rachel!</i>

44:03.100 --> 44:05.144
(THEME MUSIC PLAYING)
